oduces the concept of coping, which means neither mastering nor adapting but relates to in-between strategies and tactics reflected in practices of securing people’s way of life under conditions that are never totally under their control.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aCommunicationxSocial aspectszScandinavia. 0aSocial ecologyzScandinavia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978085745282540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780857452825423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780857452825/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK